# Next.js Development Rules

This document serves as an index for Next.js/React/TypeScript-specific development rules. Each section is detailed in its own file for better organization and maintenance.

## ⚠️ Project Context

**This is a migration project** - rewriting pix-cdp (PHP/Vue/jQuery) to pixmoto-admin (Next.js 16/React 19).

**CRITICAL**: Before implementing any feature, read:
- [Project Context](mdc:.cursor/context/project-context.md) - Goals, route mappings, implementation status, API endpoints

**Key Rules**:
1. API endpoints MUST match pix-cdp exactly
2. Routes should preserve pix-cdp structure
3. Functionality MUST match pix-cdp behavior
4. Use modern Next.js patterns (Server/Client Components)

